#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Interactive Claude session pre-cast as ds-frontend.
# Run from its own iTerm pane. Reads brief.md, writes code, logs to implementation.md.
set -euo pipefail
cd "$(dirname "$0")/.."
exec claude "You are playing the role of ds-frontend for this session (interactive, not as a one-shot subagent).

FIRST: Read these three files in order, then summarize your role back to me in one sentence so I know you loaded:
1. .claude/agents/ds-frontend.md
2. designs/context.md
3. (if it exists) designs/active/brief.md

After that, WAIT for my instructions before doing anything else. When I ask you to 'implement':
1. Re-read designs/active/brief.md, plus designs/active/evaluation.md and designs/active/design-critique.md if they exist (iteration feedback)
2. Enumerate the files you plan to edit before editing
3. Edit via Read+Edit/Write tools
4. Run 'npm run build' and fix any errors
5. Write designs/active/implementation.md with summary + files changed + notes
6. Tell me what you did

Hard rule: don't edit designs/active/brief.md, design-critique.md, or evaluation.md — those are read-only inputs from other agents.

Stay in this session. I'll come back each iteration."
